<section class="Section Section--intro Section--80vh Section--flex">
	<span class="Section-bgCredits">
		<a href="http://settlement.arc.nasa.gov/70sArtHiRes/70sArt/art.html" target="_blank">
			Torus Construction<br>
			NASA Ames Research Center
		</a>
	</span>

	<div class="Intro Container Container--full Container--centered u-textAlignCenter">
		<h1 class="Intro-title">
			<span class="Intro-radio">Radio</span>
			<span class="Intro-4000">4000</span>
		</h1>
		<p class="Intro-slogan">A single channel for everyone<br>and an infinity of great tracks curated with love.</p>
	</div>
</section>

<div class="Sections">
	<section class="Section">
		<div class="Container u-push--1">
			<a href="https://github.com/Internet4000/radio4000-manifest" class="Muted" target="_blank">
				The Radio4000 manifest (v0.1)<br>
				March 12, 2016<br>
				Berlin
			</a>
		</div>
		<div class="Container Container--centered">
			<h1 class="u-push--1"><small>Introduction, about</small> humans and algorithms</h1>
			<p>We believe each of us are engaged on a musical journey, sonic exploration of the available spectrum of sounds.</p>
			<p>We, Humans, select music according to our taste. Because it makes us dance, smile, think, not think, forget; because we like it or we think it's interesting. This is something computers can't do, even though they gave us the internet.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="Section">
		<div class="Container Container--full">
			<article class="MediaBlock">
				<div class="MediaBlock-body">
					<h1 class="u-push--1"><small>On Radio4000</small> everyone <small>has</small> one radio<small>, only one</small></h1>
					<p>
						In your unique radio you add music, any music you enjoy.<br>
						From this constrain you gain freedom. When you like a sound, add it to your radio.
					</p>
					<p>
						Your personality gives soul to your radio.<br>
						All the musics you listen, their variety, composes an harnonious whole.
						Their common denominator is the fact you liked them, so don't worry about classifying.
					</p>
				</div>
				<figure class="MediaBlock-media">
					<img src="assets/images/Torus_Exterior_AC76-0525_900.jpg" alt="" />
				</figure>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="Section">
		<div class="Container Container--full">
			<div class="Grid Grid--firstHidden">
				{{#each model.featured as |item|}}
				<div class="Grid-cell">
					{{channel-card channel=item}}
				</div>
				{{/each}}
				<div class="Grid-cell">
					<div class="ChannelCard ChannelCard--text">
						<p>Simply tap a channel to play it!</p>
						<p>Each channel is as unique as the person who crafted it</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="Section">
		<div class="Container Container--full">
			<h1 class="u-push--1"><small>Radio4000 is a music</small> tool <small>and<br></small> a service</h1>
			<div class="Grid">
				<article class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
					<h2>
						<small>A tool to</small> manage <small>your online music.</small>
					</h2>
					<p>
						All those links pointing to music you like are now stored somewhere.
					</p>
				</article>
				<article class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
					<h2>
						<small>A tool to</small> understand <small>your music discoveries.</small>
					</h2>
					<p>
						We want to provide you with some context for your music history. For example what genre it is, which label it was released on and when it came out.
						That way you'll have a better chance to dig into fresh discoveries.
					</p>
				</article>
				<article class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
					<h2>
						<small>A service </small>for and by humans.
					</h2>
					<p>
						The music content on radio4000 is only generated by Humans who want to discover and share their music selection.
						You can give yourself some rest in music digging and listen to what's around you.
						Discover some crazy tracks in the context of someone you like the taste of.
					</p>
				</article>
				<article class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
					<h2>
						<small>A service </small>to enhance discoveries.
					</h2>
					<p>
						Everyone can access your radio channel and listen to your selection. Anytime, anywhere.
						But no one needs to know who you are, it is only about music.<br>
						Aliases are cool.
					</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="Section">
		<div class="Container Container--centered">
			<div class="Grid">
				<div class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double">
					{{channel-card channel=model.featured.firstObject}}
				</div>
				<div class="Grid-cell Grid-cell--double Muted">
					<p>This channel is called <strong>{{model.featured.firstObject.title}}</strong>.</p>
					<p>Because the human behind can only have one channel, there's nowhere for the good music to hide. Highs and lows, ebbs and flows, Cambodian funk and techno. Each mix is exactly that — a mix.</p>
					<p>Click on the channel card to start exploring it.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="Section">

		<div class="Container Container--full">
			<h1 class="u-push--1">What Radio4000 stands for.</h1>
			<div class="Grid">
				<article class="Grid-cell">
					<h2>Retributions</h2>
					<p>
						No artist = no music = no Radio 4000.
						No radios channels with music = no Radio 4000.
						Let's work on a new viable ecosystem for music.
					</p>
				</article>
				<article class="Grid-cell">
					<h2>Privacy and data</h2>
					<p>
						As we said, no one needs to know who you are, Radio4000 neither.
						The only data we save about you is what's in your radio channel.
						Also you can export all your music, what's yours' yours.
					</p>
				</article>
				<article class="Grid-cell">
					<h2>Embrace the future</h2>
					<p>
						We're all here to imagine and create a music experience for year 4000
					</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="Section">
		<div class="Intro-actions Container">
			{{#if session.currentUser.channels.firstObject}}
				{{#link-to 'channel' session.currentUser.channels.firstObject class="Btn Btn--important Btn--huge" title="Your radio"}}
					Go to your “{{session.currentUser.channels.firstObject.title}}”
				{{/link-to}}
			{{else}}
				{{#link-to 'channels.new' class="Btn Btn--important Btn--huge" title="Continue to create your radio"}}
					Create your radio now
				{{/link-to}}
			{{/if}}
			{{#link-to 'channels' class="Btn Btn--huge" title="Discover music by channels"}}
				Discover radios &rarr;
			{{/link-to}}
		</div>
	</section>
</div>
